1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper specifically mentions three applications in computer vision and proposes a framework to solve semidefinite programming problems in this domain. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed framework involves an efficient alternating minimization procedure, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the complexity of general-purpose solvers for semidefinite programs and proposes a low-complexity approach to solve large-scale problems. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a numerical method to solve semidefinite programming problems and discusses the initialization scheme to avoid getting stuck in local minima. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper mentions the potential applications of semidefinite programming in control theory and proposes a framework that can handle a more general set of SDPs than previous approaches.
